de.mslab.diffbuilder

Interface DifferenceBuilder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ARIA256DifferenceBuilder, BitwiseDifferenceBuilder, BytewiseDifferenceBuilder, FullSpaceBytewiseDifferenceBuilder, NibblewiseDifferenceBuilder

    public interface DifferenceBuilder
    A value builder computes in increasing manner all n-bit/n-byte values with less or equal a maximum number of '1' bits/bytes. This can happen bit-wise, byte-wise or maybe in other fashion. This is the common interface for value builder subclasses.

        long initializeAndGetNumDifferences(int dimension,
                                  int numBytes)
                                    throws InvalidArgumentError
        Initializes the computation process and returns the number of differences.
        Returns:
        Returns the number of results.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentError - If the maxWeight is larger than the number of bits/bytes in the values n, then the whole creation process is senseless, as all possible n-bit/n-byte values will be valid and an exception is thrown. If maxWeight is less than 1, only 0 will be valid, thus exception is thrown.
